"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"\\n# ZCAM vs Other Approaches\\n\\nNumerous technologies exist for image authenticity and provenance. These solutions address different problem spaces and offer varying trade-offs.\\n\\n:::info\\nZCAM provides a complete mobile-first solution for photo authenticity: hardware-backed attestation, optional zero-knowledge proofs, embedded verification data, and a simple verified/not-verified output tailored to human-captured zPhotos.\\n:::\\n\\nBelow is a feature comparison showing what each approach provides. See the sections below for more detail.\\n\\n## Comparison Table\\n\\n| Approach | Hardware Attestation | ZK Proofs | Embedded Verification | User-friendly Output | Camera Photos | Use Case |\\n|----------|---------------------|-----------|---------------------|---------------|--------------|----------|\\n| **ZCAM** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | Complete mobile photo authenticity solution |\\n| **C2PA (generic)** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | Edit history tracking and provenance |\\n| **Physical Camera** | ❓ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | Some cameras support hardware-backed signing; support varies |\\n| **JPEG Trust** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | Trust evaluation framework (leverages C2PA) |\\n| **SynthID** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | AI watermarking and detection |\\n| **AI Content Marking** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | AI-generated content marking (watermarking or C2PA) |\\n\\n## Other tooling\\n\\n### C2PA\\n\\nC2PA is a content credential standard that creates a *verifiable history* for images.\\n\\nIt is not specific to \\\"authentic\\\" photos: C2PA can be applied to camera captures and AI-generated images alike. A C2PA manifest records origin and edit history; each manifest is signed using public-key cryptography.\\n\\n**Key differences from ZCAM:**\\n- C2PA doesn't require hardware attestation; any signing key can be used.\\n- C2PA focuses on edit history, while ZCAM focuses on capture authenticity.\\n- ZCAM uses C2PA as the container format but adds hardware-backed guarantees.\\n- C2PA is a general-purpose tool for attaching historical metadata; ZCAM focuses on proving the authenticity of an image.\\n\\nMore technical information is available in the [How it Works](/overview/how_it_works) section under C2PA.\\n\\n### JPEG Trust\\n\\nJPEG Trust provides a framework for evaluating an image's trustworthiness. It leverages C2PA manifests to build trust profiles and evaluators that help determine authenticity.\\n\\n**Key differences from ZCAM:**\\n- JPEG Trust is an evaluation framework, not a capture/verification system.\\n- It can consume ZCAM-generated C2PA manifests.\\n- Focuses on trust scoring rather than raw cryptographic verification.\\n\\n### SynthID\\n\\nSynthID (Google) is an invisible watermark framework that embeds resilient data into images. JUMBF metadata can be stripped or altered by edits; SynthID uses ML-based embeddings that a reader model can detect.\\n\\n**Key differences from ZCAM:**\\n- SynthID focuses on AI-detection; ZCAM focuses on authenticity verification.\\n- ZCAM provides cryptographic guarantees; SynthID provides probabilistic detection.\\n\\n### IPTC Photo Metadata\\n\\nIPTC Photo Metadata defines standardized fields and labels for image metadata. It is a metadata format rather than a verification system.\\n\\n**Key differences from ZCAM:**\\n- IPTC is a metadata format, not a verification system.\\n- Can be used alongside ZCAM for standardized metadata fields.\\n- No cryptographic guarantees or hardware attestation.\\n\\n### AI Content Marking\\n\\nSeveral companies provide tools for marking AI-generated content:\\n\\n- **Meta Watermarking**: Durable watermarks for AI-generated content that aim to survive cropping and edits.\\n- **OpenAI C2PA**: OpenAI-generated images include C2PA manifests indicating the generation source.\\n\\n**Key differences from ZCAM:**\\n- These solutions mark AI-generated content; ZCAM verifies authentic human-captured zPhotos.\\n- They lack hardware attestation.\\n- Different goals: provenance/marking for AI content vs. cryptographic authenticity verification for human-captured zPhotos.\\n\\n## When to Use ZCAM\\n\\nZCAM is the right choice when you need:\\n\\n- **Hardware-backed authenticity**: Guarantees that zPhotos were taken on a specific device\\n- **Cryptographic verification**: Strong cryptographic proofs versus probabilistic detection\\n- **Mobile-first**: Designed for iOS (Android support planned)\\n- **Simple verification**: Easy API that returns verified/not-verified without requiring manifest parsing\\n- **End-to-end solution**: From capture to verification with optional ZK proof integration\\n\\nConsider other approaches when:\\n\\n- You need to mark AI-generated content (use SynthID or AI Content Marking)\\n- You want a general-purpose edit history system (use generic C2PA)\\n- You need watermarking resilient to heavy editing (use SynthID)\\n- You're working with non-mobile platforms (use C2PA or other standards)\\n\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#zcam-vs-other-approaches\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>Numerous technologies exist for image authenticity and provenance. These solutions address different problem spaces and offer varying trade-offs.</p>\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"info\\\"><p>ZCAM provides a complete mobile-first solution for photo authenticity: hardware-backed attestation, optional zero-knowledge proofs, embedded verification data, and a simple verified/not-verified output tailored to human-captured zPhotos.</p></aside>\\n<p>Below is a feature comparison showing what each approach provides. See the sections below for more detail.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#zcam-vs-other-approaches\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nNumerous technologies exist for image authenticity and provenance. These solutions address different problem spaces and offer varying trade-offs.\\nZCAM provides a complete mobile-first solution for photo authenticity: hardware-backed attestation, optional zero-knowledge proofs, embedded verification data, and a simple verified/not-verified output tailored to human-captured zPhotos.\\nBelow is a feature comparison showing what each approach provides. See the sections below for more detail.\\n\",\"title\":\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#comparison-table\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Approach</th><th>Hardware Attestation</th><th>ZK Proofs</th><th>Embedded Verification</th><th>User-friendly Output</th><th>Camera Photos</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>ZCAM</strong></td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>Complete mobile photo authenticity solution</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C2PA (generic)</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>Edit history tracking and provenance</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Physical Camera</strong></td><td>❓</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>Some cameras support hardware-backed signing; support varies</td></tr><tr><td><strong>JPEG Trust</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>Trust evaluation framework (leverages C2PA)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>SynthID</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>AI watermarking and detection</td></tr><tr><td><strong>AI Content Marking</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>AI-generated content marking (watermarking or C2PA)</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#comparison-table\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nApproachHardware AttestationZK ProofsEmbedded VerificationUser-friendly OutputCamera PhotosUse CaseZCAM✅✅✅✅✅Complete mobile photo authenticity solutionC2PA (generic)❌❌✅❌✅Edit history tracking and provenancePhysical Camera❓❌✅❌✅Some cameras support hardware-backed signing; support variesJPEG Trust❌❌✅✅✅Trust evaluation framework (leverages C2PA)SynthID❌❌✅❌❌AI watermarking and detectionAI Content Marking❌❌✅❌❌AI-generated content marking (watermarking or C2PA)\\n\",\"title\":\"Comparison Table\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#other-tooling\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#other-tooling\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Other tooling\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#c2pa\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>C2PA is a content credential standard that creates a <em>verifiable history</em> for images.</p>\\n<p>It is not specific to &quot;authentic&quot; photos: C2PA can be applied to camera captures and AI-generated images alike. A C2PA manifest records origin and edit history; each manifest is signed using public-key cryptography.</p>\\n<strong>Key differences from ZCAM:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li>C2PA doesn&#x27;t require hardware attestation; any signing key can be used.</li>\\n<li>C2PA focuses on edit history, while ZCAM focuses on capture authenticity.</li>\\n<li>ZCAM uses C2PA as the container format but adds hardware-backed guarantees.</li>\\n<li>C2PA is a general-purpose tool for attaching historical metadata; ZCAM focuses on proving the authenticity of an image.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>More technical information is available in the <a href=\\\"/overview/how_it_works\\\">How it Works</a> section under C2PA.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#c2pa\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nC2PA is a content credential standard that creates a verifiable history for images.\\nIt is not specific to &quot;authentic&quot; photos: C2PA can be applied to camera captures and AI-generated images alike. A C2PA manifest records origin and edit history; each manifest is signed using public-key cryptography.\\nKey differences from ZCAM:\\n\\nC2PA doesn&#x27;t require hardware attestation; any signing key can be used.\\nC2PA focuses on edit history, while ZCAM focuses on capture authenticity.\\nZCAM uses C2PA as the container format but adds hardware-backed guarantees.\\nC2PA is a general-purpose tool for attaching historical metadata; ZCAM focuses on proving the authenticity of an image.\\n\\nMore technical information is available in the How it Works section under C2PA.\\n\",\"title\":\"C2PA\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\",\"Other tooling\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#jpeg-trust\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>JPEG Trust provides a framework for evaluating an image&#x27;s trustworthiness. It leverages C2PA manifests to build trust profiles and evaluators that help determine authenticity.</p>\\n<strong>Key differences from ZCAM:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li>JPEG Trust is an evaluation framework, not a capture/verification system.</li>\\n<li>It can consume ZCAM-generated C2PA manifests.</li>\\n<li>Focuses on trust scoring rather than raw cryptographic verification.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#jpeg-trust\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nJPEG Trust provides a framework for evaluating an image&#x27;s trustworthiness. It leverages C2PA manifests to build trust profiles and evaluators that help determine authenticity.\\nKey differences from ZCAM:\\n\\nJPEG Trust is an evaluation framework, not a capture/verification system.\\nIt can consume ZCAM-generated C2PA manifests.\\nFocuses on trust scoring rather than raw cryptographic verification.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"JPEG Trust\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\",\"Other tooling\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#synthid\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>SynthID (Google) is an invisible watermark framework that embeds resilient data into images. JUMBF metadata can be stripped or altered by edits; SynthID uses ML-based embeddings that a reader model can detect.</p>\\n<strong>Key differences from ZCAM:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li>SynthID focuses on AI-detection; ZCAM focuses on authenticity verification.</li>\\n<li>ZCAM provides cryptographic guarantees; SynthID provides probabilistic detection.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#synthid\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSynthID (Google) is an invisible watermark framework that embeds resilient data into images. JUMBF metadata can be stripped or altered by edits; SynthID uses ML-based embeddings that a reader model can detect.\\nKey differences from ZCAM:\\n\\nSynthID focuses on AI-detection; ZCAM focuses on authenticity verification.\\nZCAM provides cryptographic guarantees; SynthID provides probabilistic detection.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"SynthID\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\",\"Other tooling\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#iptc-photo-metadata\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>IPTC Photo Metadata defines standardized fields and labels for image metadata. It is a metadata format rather than a verification system.</p>\\n<strong>Key differences from ZCAM:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li>IPTC is a metadata format, not a verification system.</li>\\n<li>Can be used alongside ZCAM for standardized metadata fields.</li>\\n<li>No cryptographic guarantees or hardware attestation.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#iptc-photo-metadata\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nIPTC Photo Metadata defines standardized fields and labels for image metadata. It is a metadata format rather than a verification system.\\nKey differences from ZCAM:\\n\\nIPTC is a metadata format, not a verification system.\\nCan be used alongside ZCAM for standardized metadata fields.\\nNo cryptographic guarantees or hardware attestation.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"IPTC Photo Metadata\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\",\"Other tooling\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#ai-content-marking\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Several companies provide tools for marking AI-generated content:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Meta Watermarking</strong>: Durable watermarks for AI-generated content that aim to survive cropping and edits.</li>\\n<li><strong>OpenAI C2PA</strong>: OpenAI-generated images include C2PA manifests indicating the generation source.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<strong>Key differences from ZCAM:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li>These solutions mark AI-generated content; ZCAM verifies authentic human-captured zPhotos.</li>\\n<li>They lack hardware attestation.</li>\\n<li>Different goals: provenance/marking for AI content vs. cryptographic authenticity verification for human-captured zPhotos.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#ai-content-marking\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSeveral companies provide tools for marking AI-generated content:\\n\\nMeta Watermarking: Durable watermarks for AI-generated content that aim to survive cropping and edits.\\nOpenAI C2PA: OpenAI-generated images include C2PA manifests indicating the generation source.\\n\\nKey differences from ZCAM:\\n\\nThese solutions mark AI-generated content; ZCAM verifies authentic human-captured zPhotos.\\nThey lack hardware attestation.\\nDifferent goals: provenance/marking for AI content vs. cryptographic authenticity verification for human-captured zPhotos.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"AI Content Marking\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\",\"Other tooling\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches#when-to-use-zcam\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>ZCAM is the right choice when you need:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Hardware-backed authenticity</strong>: Guarantees that zPhotos were taken on a specific device</li>\\n<li><strong>Cryptographic verification</strong>: Strong cryptographic proofs versus probabilistic detection</li>\\n<li><strong>Mobile-first</strong>: Designed for iOS (Android support planned)</li>\\n<li><strong>Simple verification</strong>: Easy API that returns verified/not-verified without requiring manifest parsing</li>\\n<li><strong>End-to-end solution</strong>: From capture to verification with optional ZK proof integration</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Consider other approaches when:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>You need to mark AI-generated content (use SynthID or AI Content Marking)</li>\\n<li>You want a general-purpose edit history system (use generic C2PA)</li>\\n<li>You need watermarking resilient to heavy editing (use SynthID)</li>\\n<li>You&#x27;re working with non-mobile platforms (use C2PA or other standards)</li>\\n</ul>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/comparisons_to_other_approaches.mdx#when-to-use-zcam\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nZCAM is the right choice when you need:\\n\\nHardware-backed authenticity: Guarantees that zPhotos were taken on a specific device\\nCryptographic verification: Strong cryptographic proofs versus probabilistic detection\\nMobile-first: Designed for iOS (Android support planned)\\nSimple verification: Easy API that returns verified/not-verified without requiring manifest parsing\\nEnd-to-end solution: From capture to verification with optional ZK proof integration\\n\\nConsider other approaches when:\\n\\nYou need to mark AI-generated content (use SynthID or AI Content Marking)\\nYou want a general-purpose edit history system (use generic C2PA)\\nYou need watermarking resilient to heavy editing (use SynthID)\\nYou&#x27;re working with non-mobile platforms (use C2PA or other standards)\\n\",\"title\":\"When to Use ZCAM\",\"titles\":[\"ZCAM vs Other Approaches\"]}]}}"
